  "text": "In theory 1 severe hyperperfusion might lead to an increase in local pressure impairing microcirculation and thus leading to ischemia [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . In theory 2, which is supported by the frequent imaging finding of transient multifocal vessel stenoses in PRES the vasoconstriction might directly induce ischemia [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] . Age dependent differences in cerebral autovasoregulation and cellular susceptibility to ischemia might modulate these processes in both theories.",
